INSERT INTO artist (id, name, statement, notes, display)
	VALUES(303, 'max bullock',
	'<p class="artist">Max was born on 4th December 1938 near Morecambe and showed a natural artistic talent from a very young age. His first memories are of drawing stick men that he''d seen in a Daily Mail Annual, a book he still possesses, along with his very first homemade cartoon books which he did as a young child. 
In his teens Max fell in love with Jazz and taught himself to play the trumpet and over the years has played in many bands which were part of the Manchester Jazz Scene in the 60''s and 70''s. Earning his living as a piano tuner Max followed his musical and artistic ambitions, concentrating mostly on cartoon strips, a media that has been most consistently used to give his "take" on the world.</p>

<p class="artist">In the late 70''s, as a mature student, Max studied Fine Art at Manchester Polytechnic where his creativity thrived, producing prolific amounts of work in all sorts of media. Post college years saw him involved with a home-made puppet theatre, works in clay, illustrator/designer for various private commissions and, of course, more cartoons. In the late 90''s, Max suffered a series of mini strokes and with his left hand being affected his artistic output was seriously impaired. However, a decade on, he is again working with clay.</p>


<p class="artist">Of his own work Max says, "Making marks and making things seems to be a compulsion to be creative." In 2013, Max had his first ever exhibition at the age of 75 at the Old Parsonage in Didsbury, Manchester, which reflected his lifetime''s work, and was described as "diverse, moving, amusing, sad and honest."

</p>

<p class="artist"></p>',
               NULL,
	       1);

